<!-- ============ SYNERGIES ============ -->
<h2 id="synergies"><span class="tag">Putting it together</span>Table 2.4 — Muscle Synergies</h2>
<p>Compound exercises recruit a whole team: a <b>prime mover</b> to drive the motion, <b>synergists</b> to assist, and a long list of <b>stabilizers</b> to keep every joint in the chain controlled. This is why "core" and lower‑leg muscles show up as stabilizers even in an upper‑body lift.</p>

<figure>
<svg viewBox="0 0 720 250" role="img" aria-label="Muscle synergy roles in bench press and squat">
  <rect x="0" y="0" width="720" height="250" fill="#11181f" rx="12"/>
  <text x="180" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fff" font-size="15" font-weight="700">Bench Press</text>
  <g transform="translate(40,50)">
    <rect x="0" y="0" width="280" height="34" rx="8" fill="rgba(255,106,61,.18)" stroke="#ff6a3d"/>
    <text x="12" y="22" fill="#ffb59d" font-size="12" font-weight="700">Prime mover:</text><text x="120" y="22" fill="#e7edf3" font-size="12">pectoralis major</text>
    <rect x="0" y="44" width="280" height="50" rx="8" fill="rgba(40,194,160,.13)" stroke="#28c2a0"/>
    <text x="12" y="64" fill="#7fe6cf" font-size="12" font-weight="700">Synergists:</text><text x="100" y="64" fill="#e7edf3" font-size="12">anterior deltoid, triceps</text>
    <rect x="0" y="104" width="280" height="50" rx="8" fill="rgba(201,162,39,.13)" stroke="#c9a227"/>
    <text x="12" y="124" fill="#e6c659" font-size="12" font-weight="700">Stabilizers:</text><text x="104" y="124" fill="#e7edf3" font-size="12">rotator cuff, biceps</text>
  </g>
  <text x="540" y="30" text-anchor="middle" fill="#fff" font-size="15" font-weight="700">Squat</text>
